Peru:
Fujimori came for medical examinations again into the hospital
Former president Alberto Fujimori was admitted on Tuesday into a public hospital, in order to examine the muscle loss of its legs, informed its family doctor.
The 72 years old Fujimori, which 25 years detention because of offense against the human rights during its reign (1990-2000) serve, has several illnesses, including tongue cancer, which is four times operated and under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, congress member and its personal physician, said to the television that Fujimori was examined three days long in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas, in order to determine the reason for its pain and the muscle loss in the lower body members.
Aguinaga commentated that its opinion after Fujimori for humanitarian reasons could be pardoned. Nevertheless it did not wish this, because he considered it innocent.
It was operated four times at tongue cancer and he was lost 18 Kilos weight. In addition further illnesses come like heavy erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, hypertension and blood circulation problems in the legs, enumerated the physician.
Fujimori is since September 2007 in the detention center Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009 he was condemned to 25 years prison for the murder by 25 persons by the death squad of the Peruvian army, which was secretly active during its reign.
